+// shouldRenderAsTable reports whether content is a list-shaped response —
+// either a slice of structs (e.g. []Position) or a struct envelope that
+// contains one or more slice-of-struct fields (e.g. {total, offset, vaults[]}
+// or {aave[], vaults[], pendle_pt[]}). These are the shapes where a table
+// view is dramatically more readable than verbose key:value output.
+//
